==English==

===Etymology===
{{acronym}} from the United States Army "'''A'''bsent '''W'''ithout '''O'''fficial '''L'''eave."

===Adjective===
# ''([[military]] and [[generic]]):'' Absent without [[leave]] ([[permission]]).
#:''The US Army had a lot of '''AWOL''' soldiers.''

===Noun===
'''AWOL'''
# ''([[military]]):'' The status of being absent from the command and control of a military organization without being placed on leave, detached to another unit, or otherwise receiving official sanction for an absence.
# ''([[military]]):'' A person who holds AWOL status.
# ''([[generic]]):'' Somebody who is absent without permission.

